  "case_overview": {
    "headline": "Unknown 2024-10-06 price-manipulation incident",
    "what_happened": "On October 6, 2024, an attacker executed a price-manipulation attack targeting the SASHA token on Ethereum, exploiting thin liquidity conditions to extract approximately 249 ETH (~$600,000 USD). The attack was carried out through a single transaction and leveraged vulnerabilities arising from the token's shallow liquidity pools.",
    "why_it_matters": "This incident underscores the systemic risk posed by protocols integrating low-liquidity tokens as price sources or collateral. Without robust oracle protections\u2014such as TWAPs, liquidity thresholds, or manipulation-resistant feeds\u2014thinly traded tokens remain vulnerable to price manipulation attacks. DeFi protocols should enforce minimum liquidity requirements and implement circuit breakers when detecting abnormal price movements in dependent assets.",
