  "exploit_path": {
    "summary": "The attacker (0x991493900674b10bdf54bdfe95b4e043257798cf) initiated the exploit via transaction 0xd9fdc7d03eec28fc2453c5fa68eff82d4c297f436a6a5470c54ca3aecd2db17e. The attack exploited extremely thin liquidity in SASHA token pools on Ethereum. By manipulating prices across low-liquidity pairs\u2014likely using flash loans or large capital movements through Uniswap V2 (0x7a250d5630B4cF539739dF2C5dAcb4c659F2488D) and possibly Uniswap V3 (0x68b3465833fb72A70ecDF485E0e4C7bD8665Fc45)\u2014the attacker was able to artificially inflate or deflate SASHA's price to extract value from protocols relying on its on-chain price feed. The involvement of WETH (0xC02aaA39b223FE8D0A0e5C4F27eAD9083C756Cc2) confirms the attacker converted profits to native wrapped Ether. A proof-of-concept has been published by DeFiHackLabs, confirming the attack vector involved SASHA token price manipulation.",
